The plot loopholes in this are frequent and HUGE.

SPOILERS BELOW....

Catwoman and Robin don't need to be in this. They do not help tell the story, they offer no unique insights into what is happening. The two fights between Bane and Batman are not exactly inspired. Unless you consider 'I punch you, you punch me, I punch you again, you punch me' to be inspired. LAME. Really just awful.

The first time Batman and Bane fight, Bane takes all of Batman's punches without even flinching. Second time, for some reason, he cannot.

The pit Bane was born in, the hellish prison? Yeah, it isn't bad at all. Some nice folks their and master doctors who can fix and rehabilitate a broken back in a matter of weeks with nothing more than a rope and good old fashion folksy wisdom.

My favorite part was when Robin shows up at Wayne manor and reveals he "just knew" that Wayne was Batman. Just had a feeling about it. WTF!!!

Check this out.....not only does Batman recover from a broken back in a hole in the ground, it is in some foreign country. Batman is broke yet somehow finds his way back to Gotham (which is completely locked down by U.S. military forces) bypasses those military fortresses, and spends some time putting some flammable material on the side of a building in the shape of a bat, leaves a flare to be found by Gordon when his sentence of exile on the ice is carried out, and all of this takes place in a matter of minutes in the film. You don't see Batman doing ANY of those things.
